\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S4}{\ignorespaces Sensitivity analysis summary showing \(\mathrm {KCOR}(t)\) values across parameter grid. Heatmaps display \(\mathrm {KCOR}(t)\) estimates for different combinations of baseline weeks (rows) and quiet-window start offsets (columns). Across all comparisons, \(\mathrm {KCOR}(t)\) varies smoothly and modestly across a wide range of quiet-start offsets and baseline window lengths, with no qualitative changes in sign or magnitude, indicating robustness to reasonable parameter choices. All panels use a unified color scale centered at 1.0 to enable direct visual comparison across dose comparisons.}}{57}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:sensitivity_overview}{{S4}{57}{Sensitivity analysis summary showing \(\mathrm {KCOR}(t)\) values across parameter grid. Heatmaps display \(\mathrm {KCOR}(t)\) estimates for different combinations of baseline weeks (rows) and quiet-window start offsets (columns). Across all comparisons, \(\mathrm {KCOR}(t)\) varies smoothly and modestly across a wide range of quiet-start offsets and baseline window lengths, with no qualitative changes in sign or magnitude, indicating robustness to reasonable parameter choices. All panels use a unified color scale centered at 1.0 to enable direct visual comparison across dose comparisons}{figure.4}{}}
